{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019fFe5PZBpCeyoM67YZHvNL","type":"tool_result","content":"1. Moved all `github.event.pull_request.*` expressions from the shell `run:` block into `env:` variables — the standard mitigation for GHA script injection\n2. Replaced heredoc string interpolation for JSON payload with `jq -n --arg`, which properly escapes special characters and prevents JSON injection\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: No ESLint configured, hardcoded fallback session secret in server.js\n- **activity-tracker**: No ESLint configured, has real daemon logic across multiple files\n- **reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker**: MutationObserver fires storage read on every DOM mutation (perf concern), placeholder Firefox extension ID, binary zip committed\n- **waymo-sim**: No Python linter (ruff/flake8/mypy), unpinned deps in requirements.txt\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 48\n\n### What was done\n\n**pezantTools — Security fix + ESLint setup (PR #59, auto-merged)**\n\n1. **Removed hardcoded session secret:** The `express-session` middleware had a fallback `'pezant-tools-fallback-secret'` when `SESSION_SECRET` env var was missing. Now the app exits with a clear error if the variable isn't set, preventing use of a predictable secret in production.\n\n2. **Fixed `bucket` scoping bug:** In `serveProjectIndex()`, the GCS `bucket` variable was declared inside an `else` block but used outside it for metadata loading. When serving local projects, this caused a `ReferenceError`. Hoisted the declaration to function scope.\n\n3. **Added ESLint v10:** Flat config for CommonJS Node.js, `no-unused-vars` with underscore-prefixed exceptions for args/catch vars, `no-undef` for catching undefined references. Fixed 5 lint errors (unused `PROJECT_DEFAULTS` import, 3 unused catch vars, the bucket scoping bug).\n\n4. **Added lint to CI:** ESLint now runs before build in the CI workflow.\n\n**pezantTools — CI fix: Node 18 → 20/22 (PR #62, auto-merged)**\n\nTailwind CSS v4's native oxide binary doesn't support Node 18, causing CI build failures since the v4 migration (Run 38). Updated CI matrix from Node 18/20 to 20/22 and engines field to `>=20.0.0`. CI now passes on both versions.\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **activity-tracker**: No ESLint configured, has real daemon logic across multiple files\n- **reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker**: MutationObserver fires storage read on every DOM mutation (perf concern), placeholder Firefox extension ID, binary zip committed\n- **waymo-sim**: No Python linter (ruff/flake8/mypy), unpinned deps in requirements.txt\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 49\n\n### What was done\n\n**waymo-sim — Ruff linter setup + dependency pinning (PR #13, auto-merged)**\n\n1. **Added ruff linter:** Configured ruff in `pyproject.toml` with E (errors), F (pyflakes), W (warnings), and I (isort) rules. Added ruff as a dev dependency.\n\n2. **Fixed 16 lint errors across 7 files:**\n   - `agent/env.py`: removed unused `math` and `Any` imports, **added missing `Entity` import** (was used in type annotations but never imported — real bug), removed unused `state` variable assignment\n   - `engine/world.py`: removed unused `field` and `EntityType` imports\n   - `scenarios/loader.py`: removed unused `math`, `os`, `Dict` imports\n   - `viewer/renderer.py`: removed unused `pygame` import in `_draw_hud`\n   - `tests/test_env.py`: removed unused `pytest` and `World` imports\n   - `tests/test_scenarios.py`: removed unused `math` import, 2 unused `state` variables\n   - Fixed import sorting (isort) across all modules\n\n3. **Pinned dependencies with upper bounds:** Changed loose `>=` pins to bounded ranges (e.g. `gymnasium>=0.29.0,<2.0.0`) to prevent silent breaking changes from major version bumps.\n\n4. **Added lint to CI:** Ruff now runs before tests in the CI workflow.\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **activity-tracker**: No ESLint configured, has real daemon logic across multiple files\n- **reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker**: MutationObserver fires storage read on every DOM mutation (perf concern), placeholder Firefox extension ID, binary zip committed","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8245405-edbb-4c45-94db-759387969c37","uuid":"ff8fb21c-d2c9-4c04-8ee3-c772207dd345","timestamp":"2026-03-20T15:40:24.559Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"1. Moved all `github.event.pull_request.*` expressions from the shell `run:` block into `env:` variables — the standard mitigation for GHA script injection\n2. Replaced heredoc string interpolation for JSON payload with `jq -n --arg`, which properly escapes special characters and prevents JSON injection\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: No ESLint configured, hardcoded fallback session secret in server.js\n- **activity-tracker**: No ESLint configured, has real daemon logic across multiple files\n- **reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker**: MutationObserver fires storage read on every DOM mutation (perf concern), placeholder Firefox extension ID, binary zip committed\n- **waymo-sim**: No Python linter (ruff/flake8/mypy), unpinned deps in requirements.txt\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 48\n\n### What was done\n\n**pezantTools — Security fix + ESLint setup (PR #59, auto-merged)**\n\n1. **Removed hardcoded session secret:** The `express-session` middleware had a fallback `'pezant-tools-fallback-secret'` when `SESSION_SECRET` env var was missing. Now the app exits with a clear error if the variable isn't set, preventing use of a predictable secret in production.\n\n2. **Fixed `bucket` scoping bug:** In `serveProjectIndex()`, the GCS `bucket` variable was declared inside an `else` block but used outside it for metadata loading. When serving local projects, this caused a `ReferenceError`. Hoisted the declaration to function scope.\n\n3. **Added ESLint v10:** Flat config for CommonJS Node.js, `no-unused-vars` with underscore-prefixed exceptions for args/catch